FIFA on Friday announced three finalists for the Puskás Award 2022. The world’s football governing body disclosed this in a tweet via its Twitter handle. The winner will be selected by an international jury comprising a panel of FIFA Legends and registered fans from across the world on FIFA’s official website. The three nominees for the Puskás Award 2022 are:
1. Richarlison – Brazil v Serbia – 24/11/2022 2. Marcin Oleksy – Warta Poznan v Stal Rzeszow – 06/11/2022 3. Dimitri Payet – Olympique Marseille v PAOK Thessaloniki – 07/04/2022